<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>c. 1960s &#8211; Idlewild Lodge Note</strong></span>


<br>
A note found in Idlewild Lodge Kitchen.

<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 

<br>
<span style="font-size: 22px;"><i>Welcome to IDLEWILD LODGE</i></span> 


<br>
<i>"We hope that your stay with us has been a pleasant one. We have been having guests here for 33 years and for your enjoyment we offer the lodge room, porch games, badminton court with lights, etc. Feel free to call on us for anything. ANN & LES DAUTH P.S. Our weekly rates are 10% cheaper. Thank you !!!"</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>






Anna Dauth


<br>





Leslie Dauth


<br>





<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: c. 1960s</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild</i>





<br>
<i>Source: "Welcome to IDLEWILD LODGE." Dauth Family Archive [USA, Colorado, Loveland, Idlewild], c. 1960s</i>
<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1960s-idlewild-lodge-note/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/document/c-1960s-idlewild-lodge-note/</a>



</p>
